  "title": "SITE ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>Assist Project Manager to oversee all daily construction activities on site to meet project progress and quality goals.</p>\n<p>· Ensure all works are carried out in compliance with safety and environmental regulations</p>\n<p>· Ensure all works are carried out in compliance to QA/QC requirements</p>\n<p>· Convey proper instructions to subcontractors to ensure all installation works are executed in accordance with approved construction drawings details</p>\n<p>· To manage construction difficulties, safety risk and other technical issues</p>\n<p>· Prepare installation sequence &amp; micro schedule for respective façade elements according to construction drawings</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with Main Contractor, Subcontractors on all matters pertaining to site installation and quality issues</p>\n<p>· Monitor and update daily project/site progress report</p>\n<p>· Maintain proper records of Site Inspection Reports, materials deliveries and site activities</p>\n<p>· Arrange &amp; Coordinate Site Testing and Inspections with Vendors and RTO/RE</p>\n<p>· Manage and plan site materials and equipment delivery to ensure efficient use of resources</p>\n<p>· To assist Project Manager in timely submission of materials samples and mock-up for approval</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 1 year experience in Alum and Glazing Design site engineer works.</li>\n  <li>Responsible, with good organizational and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Well in Auto CAD, Microsoft Office software.</li>\n  <li>Team player with positive attitude; willing to learn.</li>\n  <li>Diploma in Civil Engineering or a related field and above.</li>\n  <li>Singapore Citizen and Permant Residence preferred. (Foreigners with relevant experience will also be considered)</li>\n</ul>",
